    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Acting Secretary of State to
                        the Consul General at Tientsin (
                        Smyth
                    )Repeated as telegram No. 1468,
                        October 19, 6 p.m., to the Ambassador in China.</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1948v08</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d550</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">550</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1948-10-16T17:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1948-10-16T17:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-10-16T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-10-16T17:00:00-05:00" n="550" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d550">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.50 Recovery/10–1248: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Consul General at Tientsin</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Smyth</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="49" xml:id="d550fn49">Repeated as telegram No. 1468,
                        October 19, 6 p.m., to the Ambassador in China.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-10-16T17:00:00-05:00">October 16, 1948—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>194. From Lapham, ECA. Reurtel 284 October 12, 1948. Glad to report ECA does not
                    have and has not had any intention alter plans assist North China. Despite
                    serious military situation agree <pb facs="0651" n="641" xml:id="pg_641"/> it
                    important for reasons you state to continue not only food and raw material
                    shipments but also plans for capital replacements. Following discussions here
                    all concerned agree this policy. [Lapham, ECA.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
